DOCUMENT();

############################################################
# Load Macros
############################################################
loadMacros(
  "PGstandard.pl",
  "PGML.pl",
  "AnswerFormatHelp.pl",
  "PCCmacros.pl",
  "PGcourse.pl",
);
COMMENT('Authored in PreTeXt');

############################################################
# Header
############################################################
TEXT(beginproblem());

############################################################
# PG Setup Code
############################################################
Context("Numeric");
Context()->variables->add(t => 'Real');
Context()->noreduce("(-x)-y","(-x)+y");

$init = random(30,100,10);
$b2 = random(2,9,1);
$b1 = $init*$b2;
$horizontal = random(200,500,50);
$m2 = random(0.1,0.9,0.1);
$m1 = $horizontal*$m2;

$func = Compute("($m1*t+$b1)/($m2*t+$b2)")->reduce;

$t1 = 100;
$f1 = $func->eval(t=>$t1);
$f1R = int($f1+0.5);

$t2 = 1000;
$f2 = $func->eval(t=>$t2);
$f2R = int($f2+0.5);

$t3 = 10000;
$f3 = $func->eval(t=>$t3);
$f3R = int($f3+0.5);

$t4 = 100000;
$f4 = $func->eval(t=>$t4);
$f4R = int($f4+0.5);

$diff = Round(abs($horizontal - $f2),0);
Context()->flags->set(tolType=>'absolute',tolerance=>$diff);

############################################################
# Body
############################################################

BEGIN_PGML
In a forest, the number of deer can be modeled by the function [`f(t)=[$func]\text{,}`] where [`t`] stands for the number of years from now. Answer the question with technology.

[@KeyboardInstructions('Round your answer to at least one decimal place.')@]**

As time goes on, the population levels off at approximately [_]{$horizontal}{10} deer living in the forest.

END_PGML

############################################################
# Solution
############################################################

BEGIN_PGML_SOLUTION
With technology, we can find [`y`]-values of a few points when [`x`]-values are very large. For example:
* [`([$t1],[$f1])`]

* [`([$t2],[$f2])`]

* [`([$t3],[$f3])`]

* [`([$t4],[$f4])`]

We can see the number of deer living in the forest is approaching [`[$horizontal]\text{.}`]

END_PGML_SOLUTION

############################################################
# End Problem
############################################################

ENDDOCUMENT();
